<row>
<cell>The modulus of a complex number z = x+iy is a non-negative real number denoted by |z| and is defined as |z| = <m>\sqrt{x^{2} + y^{2}}</m>. Geometrically, the number |z| represents the distnce between the point (x, y) and the origin.</cell>
</row>
